This paper deals with the design of a transmission technique for a single-user MISO channel, which involves optimization of the receiver constellation for constant envelope precoding. This involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM), as well as signal processing (cs.SY) and wireless networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of amplitude-and-phase shift keying (APSK) constellations, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
